content: Need more puzzles

I really enjoy this actually, it is an excellent and relaxing challenge after doing so many "normal" difficult sodukus. I love the different notation and coloring features... really this app has so much to offer compared to other soduku apps. However, this app alone overheats my phone like nothing else. Sometimes, I can't even get through one game before my phone overheats. I have talked to others with this issue as well... any tips or fixes on that would be great.
Great puzzles but needs to have ability to zoom in.
One of my favourite sudoku variants! Great puzzles :)
Worth every single cent
Love Cracking the Cryptic! Their puzzles are so diverse that I find them replayable! Very worth the price.

Another great sudoku app from Cracking the Cryptic. I still with the number buttons were bigger, and the clues when needed leave a lot to be desired. Looking forward to levels being added in the future.
very good app but the buttons are too small
Nice app, but it forgets how to undo if one resumes at a later time.
My favorite sudoku variant thus far the interface is as wonderful as all the sudoku apps from this developer
Hours of entertainment from this
Best sudoku apps by far. Check out their youtube too! Beautiful logic with hand crafted puzzles. 100% recommend to anyone who enjoys logic puzzles or sudoku!
It's great, but aren't there supposed to become new puzzles per month? Last update was 27th July... 2 months ago...
These two are getting me through lockdown. Not my favourite variant, but still fun to solve. Very poor with the update frequency.
Very good puzzles ... looking forward to other sudoku apps from them!
I need more levels (puzzles). I refresh daily in store app hoping it needs an update.. please i need more puzzles!

Awesome app. You have to like the thermo sudoku varient, but like all of the other apps by this publisher all of the puzzles are handcrafted and you have to complete some to unlock more puzzles which means that you have both a sense of progress and a fun steady increasing difficulty throughout the progression with the app.
Thermos are really fun, and these guys have made an amazing set of puzzle... my only issue with the game is that I have now finished all the puzzles, now to wait for more puzzles =)
The puzzles/sudokus are good and the controls are as smooth as in the other Goya sudoku apps. The hints can be a little bit cryptic at times.
Fantastic hand crafted puzzles, each seems to use a different little leap or trick
A great variation
Excellent. Only downside is that there aren't enough puzzles. I finished everything in 3 days.... or I am an addict.

This is the first of the (currently) 4 apps that CTC have and I love it. The choice of notations, the increasing difficulty, and if you're stuck the hints actually describe 'why' as well as 'what' number which helps me develop my solving. Great app and great puzzles!
Has been my most used app during lockdown. I knoe it has helped me get better at suduko and every puzzle has its own quirk.
Really well set, and the hints actually help you learn how the puzzles work rather than just giving you a random square.

Finished all the levels, my only gripe is that there aren't any more of them.. Also, would it be possible to add a feature so you can disable the square going red if you place a wrong number? It's all too tempting to use trial and error if you're stuck..
Beautiful and puzzling Sudoku!
No ads. No clutter. Very intuitive interface. Well selected puzzles. Best set of Sudoku puzzle apps.
Absolutely love this game.
For the experienced sudoku players, all these cracking the cryptic apps are great. Quality instead of computer generated quantity. How about combos of thermo and chess, or others?

Enjoying it, but when I get stumped, the hints are problematic more often than I would like. They refer to patterns I don't know being a novice (such as x-wing?). Also a couple of typos and logical failures which really should have been caught. Eg, a puzzle 38 hint references a column 9 thermo rows 1/2/4, when it only goes to 3, and the numbers given don't fit the 5/8 pair in the box below, which by the starting numbers and the middle thermo can only be there. I could be wrong, but it seems off.
It has been too long since new levels, please reply with when to expect more

Would love some more of the lower difficulty puzzles. Even just the one and two star ones gave me a good challenge, but there were only a couple of them and then it went straight on to three star difficulty, which were much harder for me.
Amazing app from some of the best YouTubers out there!

I really like this variant of sudoku and after following the YouTube channel for so long I had to give it a try. Puzzles are great and challenging! Would recommend 5/5! EDIT: if you didn't know, you can change the Gameplay Mode on the setting to match your preferred way of playing. This is gamechanging for me, as I was more used to the Tool mode rather than Selection mode. Give it a try!
Great games, but it burns battery like a bonfire!
Great evolving of the game and forcing you to think differently.
Bobbins!
Great games but massive battery sap. Should combine the apps into one with extra packs.
I love it! The puzzles get harder as you progress and are a lot of fun

I would like to give this game more stars but I can't in all fairness. It uses Unity, a 3D games engine, for a non-3D game; that's over kill! It uses way too much battery. A 10 min game on my old (slow) tablet took 10% of battery life and lagged. Also the games doesn't sync across devices. Which I expected, given you are trying to get the fastest time for a limited number of boards. But misgivings aside I love the game, will probably buy others from the same stable, and yes, I do recommend it.

Overall a great app. The logic flow you need to spot is also very rewarding when you finally find the next step after staring at it for 30min without putting in a digit. Only criticism is the color scheme options. Most make it difficult to see 1 or more aspects. Either the highlight matches the cell colors or is too similar to each other or... Something
Great game
Another excellent app from the creators of cracking the cryptic!
Great way to learn thermo sudoku, and some really excellent puzzles! Thermo sudoku introduces some really fun logic that I'm still getting my mind blown by.
Beautifully fun. I love all the games from cracking the cryptic. The combination of their YouTube channel and the Sudoku games like this one have really raised my skill level

Thermo sudoku's are fun, but compared to those published on the channel they seem easier and require less "thinking out of the box". It's a total of 40 sudoku's, which equals ~10h gameplay, but shorter than their other apps (afaik). The interface is well done, just the hints are really inconvenient - would be great if they could be displayed next to the grid, rather than on top of it.
Great construction. Very challenging and enjoyable.
Another masterpiece by cracking the cryptic! Thank you!
Fantastic app and fantastic channel
Lovely app, just like the other three apps from CTC. The puzzles are great and the hints are good and you learn a lot along the way.
Awesome as always!

Only done the first ten or so thus far, but the software is nice to use, has some lovy convenience features, and the puzzles are well set with satisfying aesthetics in the givens and logic in the solve.
Another Amazing Sudoku App from this developer I would totally recommend all of their Sudoku apps

Another five star App from Simon and Mark of Cracking the Cryptic fame. If you enjoy Sudoku you are going to love this variant of the game. This App is one of four Apps from Simon and Mark, the others being Classic Sudoku, Sandwich Sudoku and Chess Sudoku, all of which contain beautifully hand crafted puzzles by some of the best setters in the world.

I have bought all the other four apps and I like the puzzles which are beautifully handcrafted. All the apps are great and worth the price. I would wish there was one small change to the apps though or an option added. I am quite sure I am not the only one who would like to see it in the next update of the apps. At the very beginning of each puzzle the 'givens' are in black and the ones we add on the grid are in 'blue'. One can track the digits added especially if the 'highlight errors' have been turned off. Moreover the added digits are blue in the web app used by Simon & Mark.
Really enjoy these puzzles. These hand crafted ones are more interesting than randomly generated ones. Definitely worth the $5. Also enjoy watching the Cracking the Cryptic channel on YouTube.

Like the other apps from Cracking the Cryptic this one is stunning. Having beaten Chess Sudoku I was feeling a bit overconfident about Thermo puzzles. Let me tell you, they're so much different and just as challenging. I do recommend checking this set of puzzles out for yourself!
Great Thermo sudoku app. Wonderful YouTube channel.
Great handcrafted Sudokus! Good controls, too.
Great App, buy them all. Best Sudoku apps I have ever played. I just want more puzzles, I get stuck into the game
I love thermo sudoku! Great puzzles and enjoy watching on YT!

Edit: the bug has been fixed already! I have enjoyed the puzzles that I have played so far, this is my first time playing this variant, and it is a nice twist. The auto rotate stays on in the apl, even though it is disabled on my phone. This is unfortunate since I usually play while laying in bed and the view does not line up with my actual orientation. It would be great if this were fixed, or made an option.
Another great Sudoku game from Studio Goya and the guys from Cracking The Cryptic. I love it and would recommend all the Goya Sudoku games. Well worth the price.
As all the other apps from Simon & Mark, this is totally worth it!
Love all your apps, and this variation is a ton of fun.
